  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads H4 CSM at 100 with CHF second at 57, both confirming Risk-Off High regime as copper crashes 4.81%, silver drops 9.13%, and S&P 500 sells off 1.24%, crushing commodity-linked currencies. USDCHF is the primary expression with D1+H4 Strong Buy, H4 1212 at 78 accelerating, and the -0.77 EURUSD correlation confirming CHF and USD move in lockstep; USDCAD is the secondary play with CAD H4 CSM diverging 55 vs D1 33, a 22-point gap flagged as the most important short-term signal, with H4 1212 at 70 and D1 at 59 both rising. AUD fading divergence of 26 H4 vs 65 D1 means AUDUSD downside faces short-term exhaustion risk despite the sell signal alignment.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: USDCAD CMP 60, D1 59 accelerating, H4 70 rising \u2014 strongest dual-TF momentum in the dataset\nFading: GBPUSD CMP 36, H4 13 collapsing; NZDUSD CMP 43, H4 17 collapsing; EURUSD CMP 37, H4 13 collapsing\n\nWATCH\nUS 10Y yield at 4.595 up 3.00% steepening the curve further pressures USDJPY higher toward continuation of D1+H4 Buy alignment\nWTI Oil spike of 4.20% diverging from copper and silver collapse creates USDCAD directional conflict \u2014 a reversal in oil crushes the long\nSilver down 9.13% extending triggers AUDUSD accelerated breakdown as AUD loses commodity support across its entire AUDJPY and NZDUSD correlation cluster",
